[div class=p 
	"Once this is made, find the config that you just named in 
	[code 
		"~/.pcem/configs/
	]code
	" and open it in a text editor. Set 
	[code 
		"disc_a = /full/path/to/boot.img
	]code
	", 
	[code 
		"cdrom_drive = 200
	]code
	", and set 
	[code 
		"cdrom_path = /path/to/windows95b.iso;/path/to/tools.iso
	]code
	", substituting in the proper paths for the boot floppy, and for Windows 95 and utilities CDs.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"In 
	[code 
		"~/.pcem/pcem.cfg
	]code
	", set 
	[code 
		"confirm_on_stop_emulation = 0
	]code
	".
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Nvr 
	" NVR
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"This chipset does not pull the default NVR from a file - just make sure that in 
	[code 
		"~/.pcem/nvr/
	]code
	" there is no NVR named after your config file (e.g. if your config is named 
	[code 
		"windows95b
	]code
	", delete any file called 
	[code 
		"windows95b.ga686bx.nvr
	]code
	".)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If you've launched the machine before, you'll need to delete the 
	[code 
		".nvr
	]code
	" file as well as 
	[code 
		"~/.pcem/roms/ga686bx/flash.bin
	]code
	".
	$LF
]div
