[h3 id=Installation 
	" Installation
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"The following section outlines every step needed to recreate the outcome generated by the Windows 95 installation verification movie file if you need to perform the installation manually.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=SettingUpBios 
	" Setting up BIOS
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"On the bootup screen, press the 
	[code 
		"Delete
	]code
	" key to go to the BIOS menu. Select 
	[em 
		"BIOS Features Setup
	]em
	" and press 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" then go down to 
	[em 
		"Boot Sequence
	]em
	" and use 
	[code 
		"PageUp
	]code
	"/
	[code 
		"PageDown
	]code
	" to select 
	[em 
		"A,CDROM,C
	]em
	":
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95BIOSSetup.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This will allow you to boot from the Windows 95 boot floppy at first because the hard drive is blank, and then when the hard drive becomes bootable and the floppy is ejected it will use that instead. Press 
	[code 
		"Escape
	]code
	" and then select 
	[em 
		"Save & Exit Setup
	]em
	" on the main menu. Press 
	[code 
		"Y
	]code
	" and then 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" at the prompt.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=FdiskAndFormat 
	" Fdisk and format
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"When the PC reboots, optionally bypass loading drivers by pressing 
	[code 
		"F5
	]code
	" and wait to reach a DOS prompt. Type 
	[code 
		"fdisk
	]code
	" and hit 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	":
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95Fdisk.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Press 
	[code 
		"Y
	]code
	" and then 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" at the prompt to use FAT32 large disk support:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95FdiskFAT32.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Press 
	[code 
		"1
	]code
	" and then 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" at the prompt to create a DOS partition:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95FdiskCreateDOS.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Press 
	[code 
		"1
	]code
	" and then 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" at the prompt to create a Primary partition:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95FdiskCreatePrimary.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Press 
	[code 
		"Y
	]code
	" and then 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" at the prompt to use the maximum size and mark the partition active:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95FdiskActivate.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Press 
	[code 
		"Escape
	]code
	" at the prompt to exit 
	[em 
		"fdisk
	]em
	":
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95FdiskComplete.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Once fdisk has exited, reboot the PC. Press 
	[code 
		"1
	]code
	" and then 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" at the Windows 95 startup menu driver prompt to activate the "Load NEC IDE CDROM driver" option which will load the OAK Technology CD-ROM device driver with 1 drive present:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95LoadCDROMDriver.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"When the DOS prompt appears, type 
	[code 
		"format C:
	]code
	" and hit 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" then press 
	[code 
		"Y
	]code
	" and then 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" at the confirmation prompt:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95FormatC.png 
