[h4 id=InitialSettingsAndVoodooDriverInstall 
	" Initial settings and Voodoo driver install
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Proceed when prompted. When the system restarts, 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Switch to the next CD in the list|href=/EmulatorResources/PCem#SwappingDisks)
	" by hitting 
	[code 
		"Ctrl
	]code
	" + 
	[code 
		"Comma
	]code
	" + 
	[code 
		"Right Arrow
	]code
	" and then 
	[code 
		"Ctrl
	]code
	" + 
	[code 
		"Comma
	]code
	" + 
	[code 
		"Down Arrow
	]code
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Close the 
	[em 
		"Welcome to Windows 95
	]em
	" dialog box for the first time then open 
	[em 
		"My Computer
	]em
	" on the Desktop. Select 
	[em 
		"View
	]em
	", then 
	[em 
		"Details
	]em
	" to change the default view:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95DetailsView.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Select 
	[em 
		"View
	]em
	", then 
	[em 
		"Toolbar
	]em
	" to display the tools information at the top:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95Toolbar.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Select 
	[em 
		"View
	]em
	", then 
	[em 
		"Options
	]em
	" and select the radio box 
	[em 
		"Browse folders by using a single window
	]em
	":
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95SingleWindow.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Switch to the 
	[em 
		"View
	]em
	" tab, then select the radio box 
	[em 
		"Show all files
	]em
	" and hit 
	[em 
		"OK
	]em
	":
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95ShowAllFiles.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"In 
	[em 
		"My Computer
	]em
	", navigate to the D: drive and run the Voodoo installer:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95RunVoodoo.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"In the Voodoo installer, uncheck 'When done unzipping run' and click 
	[em 
		"Unzip
	]em
	":
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95VoodooPath.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"When the installer finishes, close the Voodoo installation window, then open the control panel (
	[em 
		"Start menu -> Control Panel
	]em
	"), open the 
	[em 
		"Mouse
	]em
	" settings, select the 
	[em 
		"Motion
	]em
	" tab, and reduce the pointer speed to 
	[em 
		"Slow
	]em
	" on the far left to disable pointer acceleration:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95SlowMouse.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Close the control panel and run 
	[em 
		"dcom95
	]em
	" to install the DCOM95 prerequisite:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95Dcom95.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"When the DCOM95 installation completes, leave its restart prompt open and run 
	[em 
		"C:\Windows\Temp\driver9x\setup
	]em
	" from 
	[em 
		"My Computer
	]em
	" to install the Voodoo driver that was previously extracted:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95VoodooDriver.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"When the driver installation completes, navigate to the 
	[em 
		"Desktop view
	]em
	" in 
	[em 
		"My Computer
	]em
	", select 
	[em 
		"Online Services
	]em
	", and press the 
	[code 
		"Delete
	]code
	" key and select 
	[em 
		"Yes
	]em
	" to move the contents to the recycle bin:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/Win95DeleteOnline.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Select 
	[em 
		"Set Up The Microsoft Network
	]em
	" and press the 
	[code 
		"Delete
	]code
	" key and select 
	[em 
		"Yes
	]em
	" to move the contents to the recycle bin:
	$LF
]div
